reviewText: I have FINALLY completed collecting all 5 seasons of Yu-Gi-Oh! Which has been something I've wanted to do since I was little. Forgot how much I truly loved this anime until I watched it all the way through.
Title: N/A

reviewText: This is it, the final season of Yugioh. In this season, we experience Atem's past about the hellish war between Atem and the darkness in ancient Egypt, and the devastating power of the Egyptian Gods. This season takes place after Atem, Kaiba, and Joey defeated Dartz and Kaiba sets up a tournament in the first half and in the last half is Atem's past also the most sad and memorial moment of all Yugioh fandom: the final duel between Atem and Yugi. The final duel will determine Atem's fate if he can stay with Yugi or vanish with his friends forever. I hope New Video Group will release GX, and 5D's in the future.
summary: The End begins, but a new future begins

reviewText: This is going to be the biggest season release, it will have seven discs instead of six, and will have three volumes. The fifth season will contain the Grand Championship arc, The Capsule Monsters saga, (added filler saga) then finally the "Dawn of the Duel" saga! Including the Pharaoh's lost memories arc as well as the ceremonial battle between Yugi & Atem to decide their fate! It just feels like the original Yu-Gi-Oh! series was just so short... I can't believe this is the final season.P.S. You can purchase this from Best Buy for only $24.99 as oppose to paying Amazon's price of $50+. Just a heads up for you buyers.
summary: This is going to be a big one!

reviewText: I'm glad to finally complete my entire yugioh collection. I'm more excited that the GRAND CHAMPIONSHIP & DAWN OF THE DUEL will finally be together as one. What I'm NOT excited about is this price. $50???...really???...I shop on amazon at least once a week & usually they have the better price, but not this time. I found this elsewhere for HALF the price. amazon dropped the ball on this one.

reviewText: I loved this show since it first premiered on kids Wb and I sometimes missed episodes but now I can own them all and catch up on the ones I missed and re-watch ones I loved the most. reviewText: I expect this set to be like the others. A cardboard slipcase, 2 DVD cases with 3-4 DVDs each. With some cool designs on the covers of each. It's the 4Kids dub, but what can you do.
